  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Clifford Chance: Access to Education for Young Children and Parents Affected by Conflict</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Funding from the Clifford Chance Foundation will enable us to launch a vital pilot project in Iraq for 2 years to address the early childhood development (ECD) needs for children and their parents, inform our wider ECD approach and contribute to access to education for children affected by conflict globally.

Early childhood (0-6 years) is the crucial period for physical, cognitive, emotional and social development. Parental support is key to a young child&#x2019;s development, but conflict and displacement can affect caregivers&#x2019; ability to provide appropriate care and impacts the support a child receives at this important time.

Location: Qayarra, Southern Mosul, Northern Iraq</narrative>
